    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Calm Gummies</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do calm gummies actually work for stress and anxiety?</summary>
      <p>Yes, when they contain clinically studied ingredients at effective doses. A 2022 systematic review in <em>Phytotherapy Research</em> found that ashwagandha supplementation reduced perceived stress by 30% and cortisol levels by 11-32%. L-Theanine has been shown to promote alpha brain wave activity within 30-40 minutes of ingestion, producing a state of calm alertness without drowsiness. Magnesium supports nervous system regulation, with deficiency linked to increased anxiety in multiple published studies. The key is choosing products with adequate dosing rather than proprietary blends with undisclosed amounts.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the difference between calm gummies and sleep gummies?</summary>
      <p>Calm gummies are designed for daytime stress relief and typically contain adaptogens like ashwagandha, amino acids like L-Theanine, and minerals like magnesium. They promote relaxation without causing drowsiness. Sleep gummies, by contrast, contain melatonin and sedative herbs like valerian root or passionflower that are intended to induce sleepiness at bedtime. Taking a sleep gummy during the day can impair alertness and cognitive function, while a calm gummy taken at night may not provide sufficient sedation for insomnia. Choose based on when you need the support.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can I take calm gummies every day?</summary>
      <p>Most calm gummies are formulated for daily use. Ashwagandha and magnesium both demonstrate cumulative benefits with consistent supplementation over 4-8 weeks. L-Theanine works acutely within 30-60 minutes and does not require buildup. However, ashwagandha should be cycled — most practitioners recommend 8-12 weeks on, followed by a 2-4 week break — to prevent potential thyroid stimulation with long-term continuous use. Always follow the manufacturer's dosing instructions and consult your healthcare provider for personalized guidance.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>When is the best time to take calm gummies?</summary>
      <p>For acute stress relief, take calm gummies 30-60 minutes before a stressful situation such as a presentation, flight, or difficult conversation. For general daily stress management, most users find morning or early afternoon dosing most effective. Ashwagandha-based formulas work best when taken consistently at the same time each day. L-Theanine-based products can be taken as needed since they produce effects within 30-40 minutes. Avoid taking calm gummies that contain magnesium on an empty stomach, as this can cause digestive discomfort.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are calm gummies safe to take with prescription medications?</summary>
      <p>Calm gummies can interact with several prescription medications. Ashwagandha may amplify the effects of thyroid medications, sedatives, benzodiazepines, and immunosuppressants. Magnesium can reduce the absorption of certain antibiotics and bisphosphonates. L-Theanine is generally well-tolerated but may enhance the effects of blood pressure medications. If you take any prescription medication — particularly for anxiety, depression, thyroid conditions, or blood pressure — consult your physician before adding a calm gummy supplement to your routine.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the best ingredient for stress relief in gummies?</summary>
      <p>It depends on the type of stress. For chronic stress with elevated cortisol, KSM-66 ashwagandha has the strongest clinical evidence, with multiple RCTs demonstrating significant cortisol reduction over 8-12 weeks. For acute situational anxiety, L-Theanine works faster, promoting alpha brain wave activity within 30-40 minutes. For stress related to magnesium deficiency — estimated to affect 50% of Americans — magnesium glycinate or citrate addresses the root cause directly. The most effective calm gummies combine two or three of these ingredients for a multi-pathway approach.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do calm gummies cause drowsiness?</summary>
      <p>Calm gummies that do not contain melatonin or valerian root should not cause drowsiness when taken at recommended doses. L-Theanine promotes relaxed alertness rather than sedation, and ashwagandha reduces cortisol without impairing cognitive function. Magnesium at high doses can have a mild relaxing effect, but this is not the same as drowsiness. If you find that a calm gummy makes you sleepy, check the label for hidden sedative ingredients like melatonin, 5-HTP, or GABA at high doses. All eight products on this list are designed for daytime use.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How long do calm gummies take to work?</summary>
      <p>The timeline depends on the active ingredient. L-Theanine produces measurable alpha brain wave changes within 30-40 minutes of ingestion. GABA-based formulas may take 30-60 minutes to produce a noticeable calming effect. Ashwagandha requires consistent daily use for 2-4 weeks before cortisol levels begin to decrease measurably, with full effects typically observed at 8-12 weeks. Magnesium supplementation can improve stress resilience within 1-2 weeks if you are deficient. For best results, combine an acute-acting ingredient like L-Theanine with a long-term adaptogen like ashwagandha.</p>
    </details>

